In case of error in any source `Mono.zip` will cause other sources to be cancelled and the return error signal. There is `Mono.zipDelayError` that will wait until all `Monos` have produced an item but if several Monos error, their exceptions are just combined.

We would need handling errors on every source using `.onErrorResume` and return non-error signal wrapping exception or result.

Here is some generic approach to wrap sources and handle results 

```
Mono.zip(wrapError(funA()), wrapError(funB()), wrapError(funC()))
       .map(res -&gt; {
            // handle res.getT1(), res.getT2() or res.getT3()
           
            // if (res.getT1().getError() != null) {
            //    ... use res.getT1().getResult()
            // }
        })
```

where
```
private &lt;T&gt; Mono&lt;ResultWrapper&lt;T&gt;&gt;  wrapError(Mono&lt;T&gt; momo) {
    return momo
            .map(res -&gt; new ResultWrapper&lt;T&gt;(res))
            .onErrorResume(e -&gt; Mono.just(new ResultWrapper&lt;T&gt;(e)));
}

class ResultWrapper&lt;T&gt; {
    private T result;
    private Throwable error;

    public ResultWrapper(T result) {
        this.result = result;
    }

    public ResultWrapper(Throwable error) {
        this.error = error;
    }

    public T getResult() {
        return result;
    }

    public Throwable getError() {
        return error;
    }
}
```

