For the ```@Autowired``` annotation according to documentation 
&gt; Fields are injected right after construction of a bean, before any config methods are invoked. Such a config field does not have to be public.
Autowired Methods.

So for property autowiring it will create a object of the class using default consructor and only after the object is created the dependencies are injected . So in your case in ```CustomLogger``` during object creation the ```myConfig``` is not injected yet and so it is null which leads to NPE.


This can be resolved by going for dependency injection using constructors

```java
@Component
public class CustomLogger {
    private final String env;
    private final LoggerConfig myConfig;
    @Autowired
    // Note : @Autowired is not really necessary for constructor autowiring in newer versions of spring
    public CustomLogger(LoggerConfig config) {
        this.myConfig = config;
        this.env = myConfig.env;  
    }
}
```
in which case the object is created along with its dependencies

#### Summary 
The question may be  how to build a custom autowired properties config in ```Spring```?
I think that you can try to follow the step below , that may be  helpful for you.
- 1. Define a Custom properties class
- 2. Add the config file ```additional-spring-configuration-metadata.json```
- 3. Wired the value which you define in step1  with spring properties
- 4. Create a Configuration class and wired the Bean into SpringContext
##### 1. Define a Custom properties class
```java
@Component
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = &quot;logger&quot;)
@Data
@Primary
public class LoggerConfig {
     public string env; // represented as &#39;logger.env&#39; in properties
    // ... other fields
}

```
##### 2. Add the config file ```additional-spring-configuration-metadata.json```
Define the spring file ```additional-spring-configuration-metadata.json``` to indicate springContext that  which properties should be wired ; You should ad d the ```additional-spring-configuration-metadata.json``` to your ```project path ```   that is ```src/main/resources/META-INF/additional-spring-configuration-metadata.json```
Below is code snippet
```
{
