      &quot;type&quot;: &quot;com.statckoverflow.properties.LoggerConfig&quot;,
      &quot;sourceType&quot;: &quot;com.statckoverflow.properties.LoggerConfig&quot;,
    }
  ],
  &quot;properties&quot;: [
   
    {
      &quot;name&quot;: &quot;logger.env&quot;,
      &quot;type&quot;: &quot;java.lang.String&quot;,
      &quot;sourceType&quot;: &quot;com.statckoverflow.properties.LoggerConfig&quot;,
      &quot;description&quot;: &quot;logger env.&quot;
    }
  ]
}
```

##### 3. Wired the value which you define in step1  with spring properties

Checkout your spring yaml or properties path , ensure that is in your resource path and then configurate  config which is define in previous  step 
the code snippet 
- properties
```
logger.env = develop
```
##### 4. Create a Configuration class and wired the Bean into SpringContext
```
@Configuration
@EnableConfigurationProperties({LoggerConfig.class})
@Slf4j
public class Config {
    @Bean
    private LoggerConfig applyLoggerConfig(@Autowired LoggerConfig config){
//  you can add some custom  configuration here 
       return config;
}
```
If you have no more custom configuration , just ignore the step4 , use the ```@Autowired```  to get Bean.
