The [NumberFormatException](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/NumberFormatException.html) occurs when the application has attempted to convert a string to one of the numeric types, but that the string does not have the appropriate format.  Basically, you tried to convert a non-number to a number.  Since you are using primitives (`int`), these cannot be null or blank.

Your message gives you all the details you need.  The String value of `&#39;&#39;` cannot assigned to a primitive value of `int`.  Try this:

```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
    String myString = &quot;&quot;;
    int myInt = Integer.parseInt(myString);
}
```

You will get the same exception.

You should add handling to your code to either prevent or deal with an empty string before you attempt to set the `int` value.

